<TITLE> Ex minister Milan transferred to Rangpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangpur, May 08 (bdnews24.com)--- Former BNP state minister ANM Ehsanul Haque Milan was transferred to Rangpur jail from Comilla early Saturday. Hundreds of BNP activists protested in front of the jail at that time. BNP's international secretary Milan was brought to Rangpur jail at around 1:00am. News of his transfer leaked out during the day and supporters started to gather in front the jail gate from the evening. The vehicle carrying Milan came in front of the jail at 12:15am. BNP activists stopped the vehicle and started to protest. The protesters demanded the release of Milan and withdrawal of all cases against him. They blocked the vehicle's path for half an hour. Later the police and prison guards freed the vehicle and took it inside the jail. The protesters continued their demonstration in front the jail for some time. Nazmun Nahar Baby, vice-president of Jatiyatabadi Mahila Dal and wife of Milan was present at the protest. She alleged that Milan was being transferred to Rangpur jail from Comilla for political revenge. She claimed that Milan was transferred in a run down microbus that took 12 hours to reach Rangpur. "It is inhuman and he is not being provided proper treatment." She claimed that the cases filed against Milan were ordered by Awami League leader Mohiuddin Khan Alamgir. bdnews
